						"description": "## Weekly Menu API\n\n### Endpoint\n\n`GET {{base_url}}/recipe/weekly-menu`\n\n### Description\n\nThis endpoint retrieves the weekly menu of recipes. It provides a structured response containing details about each recipe available for the week.\n\n### Request Method\n\n- **GET**: This method is used to request data from the specified resource.\n    \n\n### Response Format\n\n- **Status Code**: `200 OK` indicates that the request was successful.\n    \n- **Content-Type**: `application/json` signifies that the response is in JSON format.\n    \n\n### Response Body\n\nThe response body contains an array of recipe objects, each with the following properties:\n\n- `id`: A unique identifier for the recipe.\n    \n- `title`: The name of the recipe.\n    \n- `category`: The category under which the recipe falls.\n    \n- `culture`: The cultural origin of the recipe.\n    \n- `instructions`: Step-by-step instructions for preparing the recipe.\n    \n\n### Example Response\n\n``` json\n[\n    {\n        \"id\": 0,\n        \"title\": \"\",\n        \"category\": \"\",\n        \"culture\": \"\",\n        \"instructions\": \"\"\n    }\n]\n\n ```\n\nThis endpoint is useful for applications that need to display a list of recipes available for the week, allowing users to explore various culinary options."
